# midiin: lowestnote/highestnote (lines 343-344) bound which notes reach the
# voice (pitch/gate) outputs. With lowestnote = 48 and highestnote = 72, note 36
# (below) and note 80 (above) are ignored; note 60 plays. Crucially the note
# GATES are NOT affected by these bounds (line 343: "Note gates are not being
# affected by this bound"): note1 = 24 is below lowestnote yet its notegate1
# still fires while the voice path ignores it.
patch <<<
[midiin]
    lowestnote  = 48
    highestnote = 72
    pitch       = O1
    gate        = O2
    note1       = 24
    notegate1   = O3
>>>
@0 midisend trs noteon 1 36 100
@0 expect O2 0
@1 midisend trs noteon 1 60 100
@1 expect O2 1
@1 expect O1 0.3
@2 midisend trs noteoff 1 60 0
@2 expect O2 0
@3 midisend trs noteon 1 80 100
@3 expect O2 0
@4 midisend trs noteon 1 24 100
@4 expect O3 1
@4 expect O2 0
